reviews.review_text: 8-19-70 @ FILLMORE WEST THE ACOUSTIC SET IS MOTHERLOVIN' WONDERFUL!!!!!!!!AS FOR SOUND QUALITY YOU'VE PROBABLY HEARD BETTER AND YOU'VE PROBABLY HEARD WORSE,BUT DON'T LET THAT GET IN THE WAY OF CATCHING THIS SOUL LIFTING,AND MIND BENDING MORSEL OF JOY!PASS IT ON DOWN THE LINE.
wow thank u for this acostic truckin sounds fuckin great

electricity Cold Rain and Snow is dynamite, the whole sequence from China Cat thru Good Lovin' is a peak, and NFA --> Lovelight is ECSTATIC.  Let's get real, folks!!

I wasn't sure of this before, but I've determined that the best version of this show is here:
http://archive.org/details/gd1970-08-19.aud.taback.cdjones.81775.sbeok.flac16

Here you get a class act acoustic set, as attested to below--as well as a GRADE-A 1970 electric set.  Not to be slept on for those hungry for this sort of thing.

First time Ripple Played and others!!! A must have for any fan of the song Ripple, first time played - wrote in 1970 by Hunter in London.  This was also the first show for Brokedown Palace, Operator, and Truckin’.  Truckin' and Ripple are in my top ten favorite Dead songs and this is a must have for me...thank you to all the heads who over the years have put in time, effort and at times dealing with frustration to provide this music.  It is music that has molded me into who I am today.  -Born 27 years too late

good enough for me I want to know who's playing the acoustic piano? I cannot recall a record where you can hear him playing piano, particularly on this How Long Blues, during an acoustic set...

added to this review - after looking at other entries for this date... all saying its Pig, and he's really good! after 40 years mine eyes are opened again, or just more?

Good hometown show, yeah a bit sloppy, but everyone's have fun!
